make

- template
	rule: target (rule depends on target)
	tab - command to make 'rule' out of 'target'

	hello: hello.c
	tab gcc hello.c -o hello

- automatic variables
	$@ -> represents rule file
	$^ -> represents all target files
	$< -> represents first target file
	%  -> represents a pattern

using make in vim

- basic usage
	:make

- when a series of errors, :make will take you to first error.
- go to next error
	:cn

- first error
	:cerror

- last error
	:clast

- inspect the error list
	:clist
